Market Segmentation
The Vitamin D market is segmented based on type, application, and end-user industry.
By Type:
•	Vitamin D2 (Ergocalciferol) – Found in plant-based sources and supplements.
•	Vitamin D3 (Cholecalciferol) – Sourced from animal-based products and widely used in supplements and fortified foods.
By Application:
•	Dietary Supplements – Tablets, capsules, gummies, soft gels, and powders.
•	Food & Beverages – Fortified milk, cereals, juices, and infant formulas.
•	Pharmaceuticals – Used in treating Vitamin D deficiency, osteoporosis, and immune disorders.
•	Animal Feed & Pet Nutrition – Essential for livestock and pet health.
•	Cosmetics & Skincare – Used in creams and serums for skin health.
